<p><strong><img height="373" src="Images/instructional-development/Other/Grimmett, Richard.jpg" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;" width="300" />Context for a Conversation on Innovative Grading</strong><br /> Richard Grimmett</p>
<p>Thursday, March 15, 1:00 - 2:00 pm MC 372A<br /> Friday, March 11:30 - 12:30 pm MC 372A</p>
<p>There seems to be a great deal of interest in the topic of grading.  Few actually like it, whether they be faculty or students. But does it actually detract from our primary focus on learning? This presentation will offer a few ideas, some perhaps even controversial, on establishing a context of why we need dramatic innovation in the area of assessment, and what some of those innovations might look like as we seek to establish disciple-leaders.</p>
<br /> <br /> <br /><br />
<p><strong>To reserve a seat and a lunch, RSVP to <a href="mailto:instructionaldevelopment@byui.edu">InstructionalDevelopment@byui.edu</a></strong>.</p>
